The burger baskets were good, until I saw 2 gnats flying around my food. Sadly, the elderly hostess and waitress who has been working at this establishment for 6 years now, declined to take care of the issue. The elderly hostess actually had the nerve to tell me to quiet down and then tried to have the bouncer escort me out of this unsanitary hole. No wonder the burger basket was $3.50 today. If you like gnats in your burger go to Bo James, the bouncer can guarantee the kitchen is clean!!!

Horrible... To Go ordering experience.... Worst burger I have ever had. No mayo, mustard, lettuce, or tomato. Fries were over cooked as well as my cheese curds chewy and flavorless. The bartender was on her phone, vary unattentive.... I gave her an extra 5 dollar bill hoping she would know that I needed change to leave a tip.... Had to ask her to break it, after I waited for her to get off phone. I will never eat here again.
Leah!!! My fav

Went to Iowa City for the first time to go to the Badgers/Hawkeyes game. Parked the car and this was the first bar we went to. Sat down at a table ordered a round of beers when an extremely rude little hag of a woman told us the table was for dining only. There were 4 tables open when we arrived and 14 tables available when we left. Our young college student waitress was fantastic and friendly. We were informed that the hag was the actual owner of the business. Another customer requested 1 tv be turned to the Alabama game and the owner refused to turn 1 of the 12 tvs off the Ohio State game. Terrible introduction to the local establishments. I would never recommend Body Odor James to anyone. Feel bad for the young employees, who were all great, to have to work for such a miserable little turd like that.
Cheese curd burger was very good. Service, even during the Hawkeye game, was attentive.
Great food, awesome clientele.  Iowa city fixture.

Sat outside, waited a whole hour, like 60 minutes just to recieved cold fries and a burnt burger. Pricing was okay but I felt like I should have been compensated. Overall, not the best place for food , but has alright beer specials on Sunday's.

My fiancé and I had a terrible experience at Bo James. We arrived at the restaurant and noticed multiple tables open outside and went inside to be seated. Inside there were also multiple tables open. The owner approached us and stated that it would be a 15 minute wait to be seated and walked away. Confused we looked around and wondered why it was a wait as there were many open tables, it did appear though that they didn’t have many people working. When she walked by again we questioned her about the wait. She very rudely stated they were swamped and were only serving the current tables. She made no apologies about the wait or short staff. Her demeanor was so rude we instantly left and will likely never return.

Previously worked here and quit after 3 weeks because the management was absolutely awful. They treat their employees so horribly. Have worked in the restaurant industry for years and come from a family of restaurateurs and never have I ever experienced such horrible treatment. Will never support this business ever again. The management was so unprofessional and rude to their staff, and on top of this, the food was very average. I plan on reporting this business.

Went there for the first time and asked about the price of a drink. Was told it'd be $5.  The bill came and I was charged $9 for that drink.  The server admitted she'd told me the wrong price but that she couldn't do anything about it.  Terrible customer service.  You don't tell a customer one price and then charge them something completely different.  Or if you make a mistake, fix it, and not at the customer's expense. I shouldn't be paying for your mistake!  They were overall very unpleasant and rude when it came to solving the issue.
surprised its only got 2.6 stars. All my experiences there were good.

This review concerns only their tap beer.  I purchased a $3, 32 oz "Big Beer", a Bud heavy, about a month ago and has to go down as perhaps the worst beer I have ever had.  I drank maybe 8 oz. of it and could take no more.  It had to be either completely rotten beer that their distributor sold them, or they haven't cleaned lines in like ages - and my guess is the latter.  Or it's smoke in the lines that they have had from the I think 3 fires they have had originating from the kitchen over the years.
